    gschem: Fix license formatting

commit 8bcfbfc31d004ae869dff98fffea362609dc3c37
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Mon Oct 7 18:28:41 2019 +0200

    Fix licensing inconsistencies
    
    Some files in the source tree state that they are licensed under the
    GNU LGPL.  For files included from external libraries (base64, rsvg),
    this makes sense; but there are some random files in libgeda, gschem,
    and gsymcheck which state they are licensed under the GNU LGPL, as well.
    
    Since the majority of files in gEDA/gaf is licensed under the GNU GPL
    and some files (e.g., libgeda/src/s_path.c) explicitly state that they
    are based on LGPL'd code and an exception to the rule that gEDA/gaf,
    as a whole, is licensed under the GNU GPL, I assume this is an error
    and fixed the licensing information for these files.

