commit 329864aa32fa206941d85f150e26bc8798954d5c
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Mon Sep 30 11:57:49 2019 +0200

    gschem: Allow creating zero-length pins via GUI
    
    Zero-length pins are useful for NC symbols and could already be created
    by tweaking the file.  They can be manipulated via the GUI like regular
    pins, so there is really no point in not allowing users to create them.

