commit b020a08910f7298809054cc8d5917ff54674f049
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Wed Feb 13 19:50:22 2019 +0100

    gschem: Update "list-keys.scm" to current API

commit 49a813ddd937be2925a62cb6a598b70406997331
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Wed Feb 13 17:25:35 2019 +0100

    gschem: Remove empty text objects from "gschem-icons.svg"
    
    Invisible empty text objects caused 6-7 pixels of extra space to
    be added at the left and top of the "insert-symbol" icon.

commit f8a1478c59902a104a8d0c1d39f9a5f116f02695
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Wed Feb 13 18:14:24 2019 +0100

    gschem: Check size of re-generated icons
    
    In order to avoid accidentally re-generating broken icon pixmaps,
    the dimensions reported by Inkscape are now checked against the
    expected size before replacing a file.

commit 6b76f039fbefd30d1f9c129218fc0ecf23310da2
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Wed Feb 13 17:37:54 2019 +0100

    gschem: Remove spurious export hints from "gschem-icons.svg"
    
    Inkscape now uses 96dpi in order to conform to CSS.  For some icons,
    90dpi (the old default) was set as an export hint which resulted in
    these icons being exported 1-2 pixels short and blurry.

commit 116fd9e08b0c57819e1fc1539d01d077bd7347f0
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Wed Feb 13 20:10:52 2019 +0100

    gschem: Pass action object to "global-set-key"

commit 6d7d2a81cedcc85ce6520b21dadd688a5a7b8220
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 20:16:36 2019 +0100

    gschem: Update sensitivity of page actions

commit 738de516e7ad909b25e83dbfbbf26e4cc73964ff
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 19:57:03 2019 +0100

    gschem: Update sensitivity of undo/redo actions

commit 6c8801b36f088b4bc94cd2583ca59d5e9fe909c0
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 19:47:06 2019 +0100

    gschem: Recognize HTTPS in documentation= attribute

commit 175496d4d22b56e8b77e280aa01772b1ce5b3804
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 18:39:54 2019 +0100

    gschem: Update action sensibility more precisely

commit ef4b6dffc37173615713e5173dc81a1fa570f991
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 19:19:01 2019 +0100

    gschem: Make attaching attributes work as expected
    
    "Attributes / Attach Attributes" used to depend on the order in which
    objects were selected, taking the first selected object as the base
    object to attach attributes to, regardless of its type.  Now, the
    selected objects are searched for a base object of suitable type, and
    only if exactly one is found, the attributes are attached to it.

commit 037a9c167a561d942baa7762cb480656d03a0188
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 18:39:43 2019 +0100

    gschem: Make detaching attributes work as expected
    
    "Attributes / Detach Attributes" used to work on selected components
    and nets, detaching all attributes from these objects.  Now, it works
    on the selected *attributes*, allowing the user to selectively detach
    specific attributes while leaving the rest attached.

commit 5336453f0df3e5c323a0db2369499e70f7e5f5b0
Author: Roland Lutz <rlutz@hedmen.org>
Date:   Tue Feb 12 18:13:03 2019 +0100

    gschem: Don't try to descend into embedded symbol

