Date:   Sat Sep 5 07:39:09 2015 +0000

    [ba] -Add: actions and C infra for getting back annotation a "find"
    
    git-svn-id: svn://repo.hu/geda-gaf-ba/trunk@7 d4e06655-daa8-49a2-b06d-4ac0645707bb

commit a711824f5b628854f9e3a0d99c0621358a0779ac
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sun Feb 7 12:35:26 2016 +0000

    gschem: Refactor resnap logic to ensure correctness.
    
    Previously, there were code paths in the resnap logic which could lead
    to accessing uninitialised memory (reported on IRC by Gareth Edwards).
    The algorithm that chose whether to resnap or not also iterated over
    the selection twice, when once is actually enough.
    
    This patch changes the resnap logic to decide on snappability in one
    pass over the selection, ensuring that resnap only occurs if (1) there
    is at most one object selected that isn't an attribute, and (2) all
    attribute objects are attached to the same object (whether it's
    selected or not).

commit 03d06844d167d268b35c4f15c9e3a8e5495bb9a5
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Wed Feb 3 20:14:43 2016 +0000

    gschem: Use scm_c_public_variable().
    
    It's easier and clearer than using `resolve_module()`.

commit 99234fd5fb8686ecee8d4084d1dc07b1c371b8e3
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sat Jan 23 21:26:11 2016 +0000

    build: Require an external libintl.
    
    The version of intl installed in the source tree by autopoint is
    incompatible with bison 3.0 (which is the most common bison installed
    on development systems these days).  It's not unreasonable to require
    either GNU gettext or a GNU gettext internationalization library
    to be available.

commit a6026cb26708227e1e0b37591a8053ca5938bc53
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sat Jan 23 21:09:11 2016 +0000

    build: Generate an empty ChangeLog when git history unavailable
    
    When no git history is available -- for example, when the git
    repository was cloned using the `--depth` option to limit the amount
    of git history downloaded -- the changelog-generation rule can fail
    because the changelog's base git commit (i.e. the 1.0 release tag)
    isn't available in the repository.
    
    This patch makes generation of `ChangeLog` succeed in that situation,
    by creating an empty log and printing a warning to stderr.  It allows
    `make dist` and `make distcheck` to pass on shallow clones.

commit 77a2389cb3f5adb27e3ee42b36bf7c8d66ea2f7f
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter.brett@livecode.com>
Date:   Wed Jan 20 21:06:51 2016 +0000

    gschem: Refresh component library cache when reverting page.
    
    Users sometimes use "File→Revert" in the hope of fixing things up when
    symbols weren't found.
    
    1. Open page
    2. Symbols are missing
    3. Copy symbols into expected place
    4. Revert page
    
    To make this work as expected, regenerate the symbol cache on page
    revert.
    
    Closes #28.

commit 75f9616512954bd04b0e83567d41e8eed3498dd3
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Aug 6 20:47:55 2016 +0300

    gschem: Fix uninitialized variable use in o_move_cancel().
    
    This ensures that compilation is successfull.

commit a433987955843d6b55828f2dae238742abd4c449
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sat Jan 16 17:56:52 2016 +0000

    gschem: Add all system paths to GTK icon theme search path.
    
    It's necessary to put all the "icons" subdirectories of the gEDA
    system search path on the end of the GTK icon theme search path
    (because we don't necessarily know how the search path is going to
    relate to the install location).
    
    This shouldn't really be needed in the first place -- gschem-specific
    icons should be installed to the system's "hicolor" icon theme.

commit a4e6d03c746a66b0ec76ece4a68e7ca58b804097
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sat Jan 16 17:38:50 2016 +0000

    gschem: Remove "please set $GEDADATA" warning dialog.
    
    There should now *always* be a candidate system configuration path
    now.

commit 775447e4e8128d2779834b95027f735dfcfdae01
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sat Jan 16 15:53:30 2016 +0000

    gschem: Search system paths for gschem-gtkrc files.
    
    Search `eda_get_system_data_dirs()` for `gschem-gtkrc` files, and load
    the first found.  Don't load them at all if deprecated features are
    disabled.

commit 4da04329ea09420d100f2c09e4dd77067fc59a73
Author: Peter TB Brett <peter@peter-b.co.uk>
Date:   Sat Jan 16 22:21:06 2016 +0000

    gschem: Load colour maps with load-from-sys-config-dirs

