Date:   Sun Jun 5 10:34:54 2016 -0700

    libgeda: Change view bounds so symbols can be edited without translation
    
    This commit changes the left and top boundaries of the view, allowing editing
    of symbols residing near the origin.

commit 3c0c2d489097fc07878a006454af23a15ee62e2b
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 19 16:50:52 2016 +0300

    gschem: Use cairo context instead of gdk context.

commit 312502aeb0b296e5f81f059170e86e51c65629f7
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 13 15:01:20 2016 +0300

    gschem: Removed some unused color variables.

commit b3f4cfca304b5a67fe5072883437cd3be8848287
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 13 14:02:19 2016 +0300

    gschem: Removed an unused w_current variable.
    
    Currently, color variables have a separate storage and the program
    indirectly sets colors using their indexes so there is no need to keep
    the background color index in w_current if the index never changes while
    the user still have the possibility to change the background color
    itself.

commit aaccf6c2db85772680902c80b6a283775403870c
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 13 13:21:09 2016 +0300

    gschem: Fix setting of background color.
    
    Two sets of initialisation functions and arrays led to the situation
    where the background color could not be changed by e.g.
    (display-color '((background "#004000"))). This has been fixed by
    removing the function x_repaint_background_region() and using
    x_color_lookup() instead of x_get_color() to initialise the page view
    background color.

commit 849332f7c0ba8ef64dcbd434ae17ebf9d88d6b0c
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon May 30 19:36:04 2016 +0300

    Fix a typo.

