    x_window_set_current_page() a bit later.

commit 627f330fde5189dd2538375bc9a1be8aac500dff
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Dec 4 10:11:17 2015 +0300

    gschem: Get rid of o_invalidate_all().

commit e18cdd5bd4df0cbb2f9b77a72b2b809eb364dfb1
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 8 14:42:27 2015 +0300

    gschem: Fix segfaults on various actions when no page is open.

commit 81557a62a2740aba4d429e8f66a98d060394c4af
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 8 15:53:11 2015 +0300

    gschem: Get rid of checks for geometry if view page is NULL.
    
    Now it happens after H-s, H-u.
    This patch eliminates critical warnings for zooming events and events
    from h- and v-adjustment widgets.
    
    For preview widgets (in fileselect and compselect dialogs) there
    is no gtk adjustments, so we do not set their values if they
    are NULL.

commit 670c98460a15881c4fc29bb0fa0400a90b25425c
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 3 21:01:56 2015 +0300

    gschem: Split off page of page view.
    
    This allows using of GschemPageView structures even without
    underlying page, that is when page=NULL. The patch also fixes
    segfaults on yielding the following Scheme command in the gschem
    GUI if only one page is opened:
      (close-page! (active-page))

commit 43517aba280f91ee2ac1b6c67cd43cd496ca8aed
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 2 22:22:25 2015 +0300

    gschem: Fix close-page! in GUI.
    
    In gschem the close-page! procedure defined in the (geda page)
    module was overridden in order to carry out all necessary GUI
    clean up before exiting. However, this didn't work due to a typo
    in its lowlevel Scheme function name, which caused segfaults by
    using it, e.g., as GUI macro. Now it segfaults not so often :)

commit 247137745cd12aea72ad64d256c824c9a9842370
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 3 20:10:02 2015 +0300

    gschem: Simplified code a bit.

commit 76578a7aaf8c09ad66a542a88d2e441e9067f0bc
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 2 15:03:42 2015 +0300

    Fixed comment.

commit ac4c3336cacaf4c1f947f758be16beee49c70533
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 2 13:59:09 2015 +0300

    gschem: Removed unused property.

commit 8f473e5a75f7ed383128e6ed886e004270c0821f
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Nov 26 12:42:47 2015 +0300

    gschem: Factor undo code out of gschem_page_view.c.

commit d841ba0dc268db4f382bd52fc7b0f6554e709498
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 2 02:33:18 2015 +0300

    gschem: Removed obsolete doxygen comment.

commit 943109cf0979d26bcacd2e1fffb27f768d358d09
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 2 00:49:36 2015 +0300

    gschem: More accurate screen absolute object size calculation.
    
    In some cases when page view screen width is small and viewport
    world width is great the gschem_page_view_SCREENabs() function
    returned 0 due to division of integers was being done before
    multiplication by some (probably big) value. Now multiplication is
    done before division, which leads to more accurate calculation.

commit 45b6d426cbe211b5f8008a5c3ae3996d45f002d2
Author: Vladimir Zhbanov <vzhbanov@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 2 00:14:55 2015 +0300

